University officials in California and across the nation, shocked
by Monday's massacre at Virginia Polytechnic Institute and State
University, said they would review procedures for handling
threatening incidents on their campuses.
</P>
<P>
Some campus counseling centers saw an increase in students
seeking help, and some anxious parents contacted universities to
express concern -- even though for many the assault occurred
3,000 miles away. Still other parents called their children to
say they loved them.
